Name: 경복궁
Contents: Gyeongbokgung, also known as Gyeongbokgung Palace or Gyeongbok Palace, was the main royal palace of the Joseon dynasty. Built in 1395, it is located in northern Seoul, South Korea.

Name: Gyeongbokgung Palace
Contents: Free guided tours are offered of this large, 14th-century royal palace with a museum & gardens.

Name: N Seoul Tower
Contents: Opened in 1980, this iconic tower offers panoramic views of the city & a revolving restaurant.

Name: Changdeokgung
Contents: Tours are offered of this large Joseon dynasty palace & its surrounding gardens.

Name: Bukchon Hanok Village
Contents: Village dating to the 14th century filled with narrow streets lined with restored traditional homes.

Name: Lotte World
Contents: Theme park rides, water flumes & marine life exhibits in a family centred 3-in-1 adventure park.

Name: Namdaemun Market
Contents: Opened in 1964, this large area of stalls offers clothes, household goods & local items.

Name: Cheonggyecheon
Contents: Recreational area constructed around a revived stream with walkways, bridges & greenery.

Name: Deoksugung
Contents: Historic palace in the heart of Seoul offering a popular Changing of the Royal Guard ceremony.

Name: Gwanghwamun Gate
Contents: Modern reconstruction of the monumental, triple-arched main entrance gate at Gyeongbokgung Palace.

Name: Sungnyemun Gate
Contents: Restored 1300s fortress wall & pedestrian gate with a raised, pagoda-style roof & stone archway.

Name: Changgyeonggung Palace
Contents: Complex of 4 grand traditional Korean palaces, shrines & gardens for guided & self guided tours.

Name: Jongmyo Shrine
Contents: Ritual ceremonies still take place at this Confucian shrine dedicated to Joseon dynasty royals.

Name: The National Folk Museum of Korea
Contents: National museum celebrating the history, culture & lives of Korean people, established in 1946.
Image: The National Folk Museum of Korea.jpg

Name: Blue House
Contents: This complex features the executive office & official residence of South Korea's president.

Name: Banpo Bridge
Contents: Two-tiered traffic bridge with a 380-jet water fountain colorfully illuminated at night.

Name: Dongdaemun Design Plaza
Contents: Architectural-landmark events venue with futuristic design, a design market & food vendors.

Name: Heunginjimun
Contents: This restored gate was part of the Fortress Wall of Seoul built during the Joseon Dynasty.

Name: National Museum of Korea
Contents: Major building opened in 2005 to house the country's of cultural & military artifacts & artworks.

Name: 63 Building
Contents: Ultramodern 63-story tower with an IMAX cinema, a marine park & a sky deck with city views.

Name: Seoul Grand Park
Contents: Nearly 3,000 animals live in the zoos at this attraction with rose garden, art museum & theme park.

Name: War Memorial of Korea
Contents: Museum charting Korea's conflicts with exhibition rooms, monuments & an outdoor vehicle display.

Name: Seoul Forest
Contents: Vast, tree-filled park featuring a lake, bike path & roses, plus deer to feed & a butterfly house.

Name: Bongeunsa
Contents: Traditional Korean Buddhist temple complex with a 23 m Maitreya Buddha statue.

Name: Jogyesa
Contents: Main temple for Jogye Korean Buddhism with a large main hall & 7-story pagoda on site.

Name: Olympic Park
Contents: Site of Seoul 1988 Olympics with nearly a square mile of green space, sculptures & sports venues.

Name: Seoul Land
Contents: Opened to coincide with the Olympics, this family attraction is divided into 5 themed zones.

Name: Seoul Children's Grand Park
Contents: Sizable park with classic rides like a ferris wheel, plus a zoo, playground & grassy seating areas.

Name: Gyeonghuigung
Contents: Palace originally built in the 17th century by the Joseon dynasty, with an adjacent history museum.

Name: National Palace Museum of Korea
Contents: Exhibits focused on the Joseon Dynasty & royal family, with many artifacts & an audio tour.

Name: Seoul Museum of History
Contents: Free museum on the history of Seoul from prehistoric times to the present, with temporary exhibits.

Name: Leeum, Samsung Museum of Art
Contents: Audio guides are offered at this polished art museum spotlighting classic & contemporary Korean art.

Name: Dobongsan
Contents: 2,426-ft. mountain featuring sizable rock formations, trails, an ancient temple & scenic valleys.

Name: Unhyeongung
Contents: Historic complex with homes for royal & political leaders, now holding events, tours & weddings.

Name: Tapgol Park
Contents: Landscaped park housing a protected, 10-story, stone pagoda & a traditional, octagonal pavilion.

Name: Yeouido Hangang Park
Contents: Large, popular park on the river featuring scenic views, plus running paths & a swimming pool.

Name: Myeongdong Cathedral
Contents: Brick-built, 19th-century, Gothic-style Catholic cathedral with a 45m-high bell tower.

Name: Namsangol Hanok Village
Contents: Tours & cultural programs inside a recreated Korean village with 5 restored hanoks, built 1392?1910.

Name: Sinsa boulevard
Contents: Established venue lined with high-end stores, cafes & people-watching opportunities.

Name: Seolleung and Jeongneung Royal Tombs
Contents: Large city park & gathering place on burial grounds containing tombs of former kings & queen.

Name: Yangjae Citizens' Forest
Contents: Big tree-filled park with a walking path & monuments, plus tennis, basketball & volleyball courts.

Name: North Seoul Dream Forest
Contents: Densely wooded city park with cherry blossoms, maple trees, a pond, waterfall & art center.

Name: Noryangjin Fisheries Wholesale Market
Contents: Expansive wholesale & retail market with stalls offering hundreds of types of fish & seafood.

Name: 보라매공원
Contents: Big grassy park & former site of an air force academy featuring open fields, running paths & a pond.

Name: Starfield Coex Mall
Contents: Massive underground shopping mall & convention center with a theater, aquarium & restaurants.

Name: 서대문독립공원
Contents: This park with a visitor center includes a museum in a former prison & the ruins of a historic gate.

Name: Seodaemun Museum of Natural History
Contents: Modern natural history museum with dinosaur skeletons, butterflies & fossil exhibits.
